question: Does erenumab target the calcitonin gene-related peptide?
ideal_answer: No, erenumab targets the calcitonin gene-related peptide receptor.

snippets.text: Four monoclonal antibodies have been developed: one targeting the calcitonin gene-related peptide receptor (erenumab) and three targeting the calcitonin gene-related peptide (eptinezumab, fremanezumab, and galcanezumab).
